In considering vegetation groups, flammability was generally highest in IAPs, intermediate in fynbos, and lowest in thicket (
 Table 1; 
 Fig. 1). IAPs burnt at significantly higher intensity than fynbos and thicket. IAPs and fynbos showed significantly higher ignitability (shorter time-to-ignition and a greater likelihood of spontaneous ignition) than thicket.
